# CI & deploy

- Do not enable expensive or production-mutating workflows on every push unless explicitly requested; prefer `workflow_dispatch` for admin/data/backlog jobs.
- Keep deploy behind required checks; never commit secrets or log tokens.
- Fix CI by root cause (read `gh run view` / logs), not by skipping tests or masking failures.

## Before changing workflows

Inspect: `.github/workflows/`, `scripts/release_smoke.sh`, `Dockerfile`. Note env assumptions (Postgres, tokens).

## Final report

Include: workflow files changed, local checks run, remaining risks, and what must be verified on prod/Docker smoke.
